I came here for a late lunch with my uncle who had been coming here since the 70s. As someone who had lived in Spain for four years, the food wasn’t that impressive. The quality had declined over the years, is what I heard. My tortilla was too heavy on the potatoes and my spinach empanadas were just ok.  However, the place is lively. Decorated with fairly lights and football (soccer) scarves, this place is ideal to grab a beer and small tapas and churros with your friends. La Liga was playing on the TVs (present in almost every corner) in the background to upbeat Spanish music. Service was amazing too!  Don’t skip this place, just skip eating a full lunch. Get straight to the drinks, the tapas, and the churros!

I ordered from this place through Grubhub on a recent weekend visit to DC. I ordered a chicken quesadilla and added shrimp (for about $6-7 extra).  When I bit into the quesadilla I noticed something hard. They left all the shells on the shrimp! There were even pieces of the shrimp shell just cooked into the bread. Needless to say, I lost my appetite after picking all of the shells out. Very disappointed.
